programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Heroes and Heartbreak

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Message in a Bottle

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Banker and The Bum
programme.desc: A greedy banker and a good-hearted bum switch places. The bum dies, but the banker is now infused with love and generosity.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Competitive Edge
programme.desc: As a teen, Luray used to go from the beach to a tanning booth. Now she's after a corporate career, and doesn't want to look like an old lady compared to the other job candidates.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: The Old Look Is In Remission
programme.desc: Bobbi's appearance has suffered greatly due to her constant medical treatments and recent mastectomy. After losing her hair and her left breast, she is ready for a change, and has called upon our team of experts to help her through the process.
programme.sub-title: The Old Look Is In Remission

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Overhauling Momma
programme.desc: Wendy's fought the battle of the bulge her entire life, but now she's gone from a size 30 to a size 6 and is enjoying a more active lifestyle. Dermatology and cosmetic dentistry bring her face in line with her new body. Will she go from tired to admired?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: She’s Cookin’ Now!
programme.desc: Wendy is a house cleaner with bigger aspirations. A single mother for 15 years, Wendy recently remarried, and with a duel income, it's time for her to follow her dreams of becoming a professional chef. The only problem – her looks aren't exactly 5 Star.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bernie Sharp
programme.desc: Presenter and stylist Nicky Hambleton-Jones uses every trick in the book to make someone look dramatically younger. What will it take to transform the bedraggled and drawn features of prison officer Bernie Sharp?

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Sharon Evans
programme.desc: 45 year old Welsh farmer Sharon Evans has so many animals to tend to that she's stopped looking after herself. Nicky Hambleton-Jones calls in the full cavalry on this one. Standby for one of the most breathtaking transformations of the series.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Oh, To Be a Kid Again!
programme.desc: Katrina dropped out of school and became a needed parent to her younger siblings. Her looks went south and her social life became non-existent, so Katrina turned to food for comfort. Time to make Katrina look 10 Years Younger!
programme.sub-title: Oh, To Be a Kid Again!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Turning That Frown Upside Down
programme.desc: Angela's made such a habit of hiding her discolored teeth that she's developed a permanent frown. She's pursuing a career as a comedienne, but it's hard for her to laugh about the state of her looks. She feels like the clock is ticking.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From ‘Stache to Flash
programme.desc: Jerry, a caring husband, father of three, and new grandfather, has been hiding his teeth behind a moustache for years! With his style stuck in the 70's, it's our goal to help Jerry flash forward as we try to make Jerry look 10 Years Younger!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Carole Ward
programme.desc: Nicky Hambleton-Jones and the team come to the rescue of 47-year-old Carole Ward who feels very unglamorous.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: From Scrubs to Stilettos
programme.desc: Lisa works double shifts as a nurse and is also a single mom to a teenage son. After burning the candle at both ends for so long, it is finally showing up in her appearance. Our team is going to give this busy career mom some serious pampering.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Breaking Ground On A New Look
programme.desc: Dane's been working in the sun without coverage since he was 14 years old, and hasn't been to the dentist in 13 years. He's a derm and dental bad boy who needs to be scared straight, not only for himself, but for his daughters and fiancé as well.
programme.sub-title: Breaking Ground On A New Look

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Starting Over
programme.desc: Elyse is a recently divorced mother of two, trying to start her new life. She has found it difficult to stay in shape, and feels stress, UV rays and time have caught up with her. Now ready to re-enter the dating game, our coaches help get her into shape.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Runaway Ready
programme.desc: Joslyn modeled in college, and was a woman who always took care of the way she looked. After becoming a mother, the years of neglect have caught up to her. Will our experts be able to make Joslyn runway ready?

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: The Master Key
programme.desc: When a pregnant mother and her two young sons are brutally slain, pressure mounts for the CSPD to catch the cold-blooded monster who did it.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Joker In the Pack
programme.desc: A card game is interrupted by gunfire, leaving a young man dead. Lt. Joe Kenda soon learns the seeds of his destruction were sewn earlier the same day.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: I Will Hunt You Down
programme.desc: When two escaped inmates surface in Colorado Springs, it’s up to Lt. Joe Kenda and his Fugitive Unit to bring them to justice.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Comes Knocking
programme.desc: Neighbors are aghast when Ernestine Addison and her teen son Bobby are gunned down in cold blood. The case heats up when Kenda receives word that the killer’s murderous rampage isn’t over just yet.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Bad Moon Rising
programme.desc: Night before Halloween, a real-life nightmare unfolds when a young man is found clinging to life. The case takes a dark turn when Lt. Joe Kenda learns there is a second victim somewhere in the woods.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Innocence
programme.desc: War hero Carl Taylor is beaten to death in the back of an empty semi truck, for no apparent reason. Lt Joe Kenda notices an unusual pattern in the victim’s head wounds.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Murder Bites
programme.desc: A young woman is found naked and strangled in a park not 200 yards from her home. It isn’t until Lt. Joe Kenda rethinks the entire case that he realizes someone has been lying.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Sadie and Calder
programme.desc: Allen and Erin Carrasco ‘s Basset Hound Sadie whines and moans whenever Allen is around. Blue Heeler mix Calder is a great dog by day, but bedtime rituals unleash unwelcome night terrors.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Bull-Whipped
programme.desc: Aggressive bulldog Hugo is sent to canine rehab, and fellow bulldog Crusty must overcome his dominance issues if he's ever going to enjoy walks.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: The Language of Scrout
programme.desc: A Doberman Mix has taken control of his family home; an animal communicator calls for back-up with her Doberman Pinscher; and a comedienne enlists Cesar's help for her two temperamental rescue dogs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar's Worst Bite
programme.desc: Holly, a Labrador puppy, displays severe food aggression; a women's shelter will take a needy woman and her pit bull, Tucker, but Cesar must help the dog become less protective first.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cotton, Ricky, and Lila & Duke
programme.desc: An American Eskimo watchdog who takes his role too far; a Shibu Inu with a mean streak; a boxer who was attached by another dog one day in the park, and has since become more aggressive.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Not So Home Sweet Home
programme.desc: A Border Collie is overly protective of her owner, nipping at anyone who comes near her. A Police Officer rescued a German shepherd, who is people and dog aggressive and always ready for a fight.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar Down Under
programme.desc: Paul Watson can't stop his great Dane, from biting at him. Andrea and Adrian avoid taking their Bearded Collie to the dog park because of her. Cesar travels down under to tame them.
programme.sub-title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar Down Under

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Molly, Jane, and Genoa
programme.desc: Cesar helps Molly, a blue heeler in Nebraska, get over the dangerous behavior of chasing and biting the tires of moving. An American Eskimo/border collie mix in Chicago, just won't go for a walk.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: My Strange Addiction Special 2
programme.desc: In this one-hour special, we revisit six of our addicts whose stories shocked the world. Tune in for exclusive never before seen footage in this special episode.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Airline Addict_Crazy for Capybaras
programme.desc: Anthony has been collecting aviation memorabilia since he was 5. Melanie is crazy about her pet capybara, Gari, taking him for walks and teaching him tricks.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Casting / Psychics
programme.desc: Profiled are Kevin, who constantly covers his body in plaster casts even though he is not injured, and Melissa who is incapable of making a decision without a consulting a psychic.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Gas Sniffer/Teddy Bear Obsession
programme.desc: For more than 30 years, Theresa has been addicted to smelling gasoline. Meanwhile, former drug-addict Krista has 12 'children' -- all of which are teddy bears.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Addicted to Inflatables/Butt Injection Addict
programme.desc: Mark has been addicted to his 15 inflatable pool toys, eating with them, sleeping with them and even bathing them. Karmello has been getting black market butt injections for the last three years.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Dirt/Extreme Toenails
programme.desc: Kristie has eaten dirt every day for the last 30 years, consuming more than five tons since her addiction began. Meanwhile, Ayanna is addicted to growing her toenails.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Eats Cleanser/Tanner
programme.desc: Ever since she was twelve Crystle has been obsessed with eating household cleanser. Samantha is addicted to tanning and visits multiple tanning salons in order to get her fix.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: My Crazy Obsession Christmas Spcl 1
programme.desc: My Crazy Obsession: Christmas Collection takes you inside the lives of extreme collectors who have taken holiday decorating to the max. For these obsessed collectors, it's Christmas year round.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Love Bunnies_ World's Strongest Family
programme.desc: The Best family is so obsessed with their own strength that they spend countless hours lifting weights. Candace and Steve's collection of bunny items has reached nearly 30,000 pieces.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: Raggedy Ann_A Rat's Tale
programme.desc: Chantal’s 19 pet rats are more than just pets; she considers them her children. Robyn loves to share her obsession with Raggedy Ann and she tries to convert new Raggedy believers.

programme.title: My Crazy Obsession: 5,000 Kids_Tickled Pink
programme.desc: Pat and Joe are passionate about their extreme collection of over 5,000 infamous kid dolls. Kitty Kay Sera is completely obsessed with the color pink. She even wears pink clothes and eats pink food.

programme.title: My Strange Addiction: Ventriloquist/Cat Lady
programme.desc: April's addiction to her puppets has gotten so strong she can't go anywhere without them. Debbie is severely allergic to cats, but has over twenty of them, leaving her in isolation.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bourbon St. to Bayous
programme.desc: The city of New Orleans is made up of 72 different neighborhoods, each with their own distinct bayou charm. Gene and his fiancée Elizabeth are looking for a Big Easy home.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Bayou Ski Town
programme.desc: Woodville, Mississippi is a bayou ski town – waterskiing that is. Bayou newlyweds Dustin and Stephanie are looking find their own piece of waterfront heaven where they can boat, and ski!

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Floating for a Bargain
programme.desc: Mac and his wife, Kelsey, are looking for a home for them and their 5-month-old daughter on the tubing paradise, the Bogue Chitto River.

programme.title: Buying Bayou: Gator Island
programme.desc: Alligator Point, Florida is so swampy and wild, it’s known as the Forgotten Coast. This area feels more bayou than tropical, which is exactly why water taxi driver Richard and Julia want a waterfront home here.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Off the Base
programme.desc: There’s a lot of pressure living life on a submarine—that’s why Naval Officer Jeremy Brown and his wife, Nikki, want to move out of Pearl Harbor and into the lush Hawaiian Mountains.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Turnin’ Up The Heat
programme.desc: Maui is where people come to escape. That’s exactly why Patrick and Jeannie came here from cold Massachusetts.They want to upgrade their condo for their own piece of Maui.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Jungle Fever
programme.desc: Maui’s filled with deserts by the coast and lush jungles in the mountains, many people come here to escape. Jeff and Pam want to get away from the desert and into the jungle, but will it be too wild?

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Flying Kauai
programme.desc: Gerry and Julie moved to Kauai searching for adventure. Gerry is a pilot and hang glider; he would love to find a property where he can fuse his love of excitement with functional living.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Backyard Survival
programme.desc: Life on Oahu is so expensive, for some families, the only way to get by is to grow your own food. That’s what Erik and Amy Eck want, a backyard farm to teach their baby, how to live off the land.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Volcano Living
programme.desc: The Big Island is the only place in Hawaii you’ll find active volcanoes. No matter where you are, you’re in the path of lava. Joel and Lani are willing to take the risk, but how close will they get?

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Big Island Project
programme.desc: Jesse and his wife Tracy have been living in a tent on the Big Island for three years. They’re ready to upgrade their lifestyle but still looking for a house where they can still live off the grid.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Big Apple to Big Island
programme.desc: DeVante’s making the move from the Big Apple to the Big Island. But for he and his girlfriend, Jen, life out here is way different than they imagined – there’s volcanoes, tsunamis, even giant bugs.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: Boar Island
programme.desc: Martin and Connie came to Kauai from Los Angeles. Between the constant rain, sea creatures, and wild boars, life is rustic, but they’re here to stay, and want the perfect home for their adventure.

programme.title: Buying Hawaii: One Way Ticket
programme.desc: Many people dream of living in Hawaii, and Tucker and Nicole have made that dream a reality. After huge life events, they bought one-way tickets to Oahu and are looking to put down permanent roots.
